==English==
===Etymology===
From the latin carina, a boat keel.

===Adjective===
'''carinate'''

# Keel-shaped, as in a boat's [[keel]].
#:''The actuating pawl is '''carinate'''.''
# Of a bird, having a keeled [[breastbone]] allowing the attachment of flight [[muscle]]s.

